{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λευκᾰθ-ίζω</b>, <br /> <b>to be white</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.27 (codices _optative_), “PLeid.X.” 84, “Corpus Glossariorum Latinorum” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of spots on the body, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.13.38; [τρίχες] λευκαθίζουσαι 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 22.9; αἶγες χιόνι λ. [prev. author] 45.3, compare 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 17.8, 9 \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]; λ. οἱ λόφοι, of snow-clad hills, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.30; οἰκία λ. γύψῳ 1st-2nd c.AD: Epictetus Philosophus “Gnomologium” 43 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of fluids in the eye, <b>to be colourless</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Cassius Medicus “Physici et Medici Graeci Minores” 27 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; of eyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “Πυρρώνειοι ὑποτυπώσεις” 1.44:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, λελευκαθισμένη <b>clad in white</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Cant.8.5 \">LXX</a>]. (λευκανθ- is read in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>], but is against the metre, also in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus, 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus, 1st-2nd c.AD: Epictetus Philosophus, 3rd c.AD: Cassius Medicus, and 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus, and is variant in Hdt.[same place], LXX.Cant. [same place]\">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]; compare λευκαθέω, ὑπολευκαθίζω.)","strongNumber":"G8186","accentedUnicode":"λευκανθίζω","shortDef":"be white","mediumDef":"be white","stepGloss":"be white","stepTransliteration":"leukanthizō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}